name: Boulder Public Library
directions: First and Second Floors of the Main library South Building; between the entrance off of Arapahoe and the library bridge.
comment: Mindblowing restrooms.  Beautiful, well-appointed, inclusive, restrooms for all.  Public art is infused throughout this space which offers 7 private toilet rooms on each floor, inside of a common area space for handwashing, diaper-changing, etc.  Restrooms have state-of-the-art hand washers and dryers, as well as paper towels, and diaper changing stations.  As an alternative, visitors can choose to select traditional gender-specific restrooms that are available nearby.  The all gender, inclusive restrooms feature translation to 8 languages, an original art mural at the entrance, with public art replicated in each individual toilet room.  Revolutionary concept, truly has to be seen to be enjoyed!
